Install MariaDB;

sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install mariadb-server
sudo mysql_secure_installation

sudo mysql -u root -p
CREATE DATABASE dns_manager;
CREATE USER 'dnsadmin'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'Dn5Manage@r';
GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON dns_manager.* TO 'dnsadmin'@'localhost';
FLUSH PRIVILEGES;
EXIT;



Running the app;

Init the DB # python setup_database.py
Run the app # python run.py
Use Gunicorn/reverse proxy for prod env # gunicorn -w 4 -b 0.0.0.0:5000 "run:create_app()" , use nginx.
